(Decision
    "Two follow-up cleanups in signal-frame after the macro migration: (1) collapse Operation<Payload> out of Request<Payload> entirely. With SignalVerb removed, Operation is a transparent {payload} wrapper carrying no semantic content; consumers see Request<Payload> = NonEmpty<Payload>. If a contract ever needs per-op metadata it goes in the payload type, not in a kernel wrapper. (2) Drop Request::check() entirely. With the universal verb-shaped rules gone, the function always returns Ok and is dead API. Channel-specific validation belongs in daemon executors or in payload-level constructors, not in a kernel function that lies about doing work."
    "I concur"
    "Resolving the two design smells flagged in operator report 138 §'What remains' #4. The macro migration succeeded; these cleanups bring the kernel types into alignment with the new direction."
    Maximum
    2026-05-19T20:50:00Z)

